    "A DenseNet-like architecture was used as the CNN component due to its successful application in the recognition of Raman spectra 67, 68, providing good performance and fast convergence while being relatively simple.",
    "DenseNet is a type of deep-learning NN where sequences of input data are processed stepwise.",
